## 🐛 Bug Report

When I generate an Excel file with a table, and add column formatting, I see the formatted data perfectly in Preview mode of my Mac finder, but when I open it, Excel needs to repair the file, and formatting is lost.
Lib version: 4.2.0
Browser: Chrome 88.0.4324.192

## Steps To Reproduce
Code to reproduce:

```javascript
        var data = {
            "columns":[{
                "name": "A",
                "style":{
                    "numFmt":"yyyy"
                }
            }],
            "rows":[
                [new Date()]
            ]
        };
	workbook = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
	worksheet = workbook.addWorksheet('Sheet1');
	worksheet.columns = data.columns;
	worksheet.addTable({
		name: "table1",
		ref: 'A1',
		columns: data.columns,
		rows: data.rows,
	});
	workbook.xlsx.writeBuffer().then(function (data) {
            const blob = new Blob([data],
               { type: 'application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet' });
            const url = window.URL.createObjectURL(blob);
            const anchor = document.createElement('a');
            anchor.href = url;
            anchor.download = 'download.xlsx';
            anchor.click();
            window.URL.revokeObjectURL(url);
       });
```

## The expected behaviour:

Excel file would open without repair, but needs repair. In the Preview mode, it actually works and shows the correct value (year in this example), however when I double click and want to open it it requires a fix. 

## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):
sorry, no idea :)

